The paper focuses on the issue of obsolete answers on Stack Overflow, which is a platform for software developers to seek and share knowledge. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also discusses the characteristics of obsolete answers, which may be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper mentions the need for Stack Overflow to develop mechanisms to maintain answers, which may be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.DB (Databases) and cs.PL (Programming Languages).
